Question 5

Call Options

Consider a 111-period binomial model with R=1.02R=1.02R=1.02, S0=100S_0 = 100S0​=100,

u=1/d=1.05u=1/d= 1.05u=1/d=1.05. Compute the value of a European call option on the stock

with strike K=102K=102K=102. The stock does not pay dividends.

Please submit your answer rounded to two decimal places. So for example, if your answer is 3.45673.45673.4567 then you should submit an answer of 3.463.463.46.
1 / 1 point
2.04
Correct

The arbitrage-free value is C0=1RE0Q[C1]=1R[qCu+(1−q)Cd]C_0 = \frac{1}{R} E^{Q}_0[C_1] = \frac{1}{R} \left[q C_u + (1-q) C_d \right] C0​=R1​E0Q​[C1​]=R1​[qCu​+(1−q)Cd​] where q=R−du−dq = \frac{R-d}{u-d}q=u−dR−d​, 1−q=u−Ru−d1-q=\frac{u-R}{u-d}1−q=u−du−R​, Cu=3C_u = 3Cu​=3 and

Cd=0C_d=0Cd​=0.

Therefore C0=qCu/R=2.0373C_0 = qC_u/R = 2.0373C0​=qCu​/R=2.0373.
